content:
if fs.exists("conf") == false then
    shell.run("pastebin get 38M5cNbZ conf")
    term.clear()
end

local OffsetValue = 3 -- How much you want your shield to be configured forward
local shield = peripheral.find("warpdriveForceFieldProjector")
local laser = peripheral.find("warpdriveLaserCamera")
local lever = "front" -- format: front,back,left,right,top,bottom ONLY
local safedist = 15 -- Set Safe Distance
laser.beamFrequency(1420) -- Sets the frequency of the laser to 1420

-- initial message
print("Control System Online, Toggle Redstone To Toggle Shields, Press C to Configure")

local _, upgrades = shield.getUpgrades()
--- this function is really janky but I don't want to make it better
function getRange()
    if upgrades:match("1/4 x Range") then
        return 1
    elseif upgrades:match("2/4 x Range") then
        return 2
    elseif upgrades:match("3/4 x Range") then
        return 3
    elseif upgrades:match("4/4 x Range") then
        return 4
    elseif upgrades:match("0/4 x Range") then
        return 0
    end
end
 
Size = getRange() * 16

while true do
    os.sleep(0.5)
    local event, key = os.pullEvent()

    if event == "key" then
        -- keys are represented by numbers, the number for 'C' is 46
        if key == 46 then
            print("C key pressed, running 'conf' script...")
            shell.run("conf")
        end
    elseif event == "laserScanning" then
        -- Laser scan target position
        local type, lx, ly, lz, block = laser.getScanResult()
        lx, ly, lz = tonumber(lx), tonumber(ly), tonumber(lz) -- Convert to numbers

        -- Shield position
        local fx, fy, fz = shield.getLocalPosition()

        function shieldOffset()
            -- Calculate direction vector from shield position to laser scan target position
            local dx = lx - fx
            local dy = ly - fy
            local dz = lz - fz

            -- Calculate the length of the direction vector
            local distance = math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy + dz * dz)

            -- Normalize the direction vector to have a length of 1 (unit vector)
            dx = dx / distance
            dy = dy / distance
            dz = dz / distance

            -- Calculate the final target position by extending the direction vector by OffsetValue
            local t1x = lx + dx * OffsetValue
            local t1y = ly + dy * OffsetValue
            local t1z = lz + dz * OffsetValue

            return t1x, t1y, t1z, distance -- Return the final target position and distance
        end

        local t1x, t1y, t1z, distance = shieldOffset()

        tx = (t1x - fx) / Size
        ty = (t1y - fy) / Size
        tz = (t1z - fz) / Size

        if distance < safedist then
            print("Target is too Close! Shield Disabled!")
            shield.enable(false) -- Disable shield if too close
            elseif distance > safedist and distance > Size then
            print("Target is too Far! Shield Disabled!")
            shield.enable(false) -- Disable shield if too far
        elseif distance > safedist and distance < Size then
            shield.translation(tx, ty, tz)
        end
    elseif event == "redstone" then
        local _, _, _, distance = shieldOffset()
        local on = redstone.getAnalogInput(lever)
        if on > 6 and distance > safedist and distance < Size then
            shield.enable(true)
        elseif on > 6 and distance > safedist and distance > Size then
            print("Target is too Far! Shield Disabled!")
            shield.enable(false) -- Disable shield if too far
        elseif on > 6 and distance < safedist then
            shield.enable(false)
            print("Target is too Close! Shield Disabled!")
        elseif on < 5 then
            shield.enable(false)
        end
    end
end

content:
if fs.exists("conf") == false then
    shell.run("pastebin get 38M5cNbZ conf")
    term.clear()
end

local OffsetValue = 5 -- How much you want your shield to be configured forward
local shield = peripheral.find("warpdriveForceFieldProjector")
local laser = peripheral.find("warpdriveLaserCamera")
local lever = "front" -- format: front,back,left,right,top,bottom ONLY
local safedist = 15 -- Set Safe Distance
laser.beamFrequency(1420) -- Sets the frequency of the laser to 1420

-- initial message
print("Control System Online, Toggle Redstone To Toggle Shields, Press C to Configure")

local _, upgrades = shield.getUpgrades()

local lx, ly, lz = nil, nil, nil

-- Function definitions moved out of the loop

function getRange()
    if upgrades:match("1/4 x Range") then
        return 1
    elseif upgrades:match("2/4 x Range") then
        return 2
    elseif upgrades:match("3/4 x Range") then
        return 3
    elseif upgrades:match("4/4 x Range") then
        return 4
    else -- Added else clause to handle no match case
        return 0
    end
end

function shieldOffset()
    if lx and ly and lz then
        -- Shield position
        local fx, fy, fz = shield.getLocalPosition()

        -- Calculate direction vector from shield position to laser scan target position
        local dx = lx - fx
        local dy = ly - fy
        local dz = lz - fz

        -- Calculate the length of the direction vector
        local distance = math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy + dz * dz)

        -- Normalize the direction vector to have a length of 1 (unit vector)
        dx = dx / distance
        dy = dy / distance
        dz = dz / distance

        -- Calculate the final target position by extending the direction vector by OffsetValue
        local t1x = lx + dx * OffsetValue
        local t1y = ly + dy * OffsetValue
        local t1z = lz + dz * OffsetValue

        return t1x, t1y, t1z, distance -- Return the final target position and distance
    end
end

Size = getRange() * 16

while true do
    os.sleep(0.5)
    local event, key = os.pullEvent()

    if event == "key" then
        -- keys are represented by numbers, the number for 'C' is 46
        if key == 46 then
            print("C key pressed, running 'conf' script...")
            shell.run("conf")
        end
    elseif event == "laserScanning" then
        -- Laser scan target position
        local type, lx, ly, lz, block = laser.getScanResult()
        lx, ly, lz = tonumber(lx), tonumber(ly), tonumber(lz) -- Convert to numbers

        local t1x, t1y, t1z, distance = shieldOffset()

        tx = (t1x - fx) / Size
        ty = (t1y - fy) / Size
        tz = (t1z - fz) / Size

        if distance < safedist then
            print("Target is too Close! Shield Disabled!")
            shield.enable(false) -- Disable shield if too close
        elseif distance > safedist then
            shield.translation(tx, ty, tz)
        end
    elseif event == "redstone" then
        local _, _, _, distance = shieldOffset()
        local on = redstone.getAnalogInput(lever)
        if on > 6 and distance > safedist then
            shield.enable(true)
        elseif on > 6 and distance < safedist then
            shield.enable(false)
            print("Target is too Close! Shield Disabled!")
        elseif on < 5 then
            shield.enable(false)
        end
    end
end

select
	aa.gate_in_id,
	coalesce(aa.balance, 0) as balance,
	bb.terminal_name as terminal,
	dd.station_name as station,
	aa.card_issuer as bank_name,
	CONCAT(to_char(aa.created_on, 'dd-mm-YYYY'), ', ', to_char(aa.created_on, 'HH24:MI:SS')) as gate_in_on,
	gg.terminal_name as terminal_before_in,
	ii.card_type_name as type_card,
	ee.station_name as station_before_in,
	CONCAT(to_char(aa.gate_in_before_on, 'dd-mm-YYYY'), ', ', to_char(aa.gate_in_before_on, 'HH24:MI:SS')) as gate_before_in,
	hh.terminal_name as terminal_before_out,
	ff.station_name as station_before_out,
	aa.card_number,
	cc.bank_name,
	aa.created_on,
	CONCAT(to_char(aa.gate_out_before_on, 'dd-mm-YYYY'), ', ', to_char(aa.gate_out_before_on, 'HH24:MI:SS')) as gate_before_out,
	case
		when jj.uid is not null then jj.uid
		when ll.uid is not null then ll.uid
		else null
	end as uid,
	case
		when jj.name is not null then jj.name
		when ll.name is not null then ll.name
		else null
	end as name,
	case
		when jj.nik is not null then jj.nik
		when ll.nik is not null then ll.nik
		else null
	end as nik,
	case
		when jj.institution_name is not null then jj.institution_name
		when ll.institution_name is not null then ll.institution_name
		else null
	end as institution_name,
	case
		when kk.name_type is not null then kk.name_type
		when ll.card_number is not null then 'Family Trip'
		else null
	end as subs_card_type_name
from
	trx.t_trx_gate_in_kue aa
left join master.t_mtr_device_terminal bb on
	aa.terminal_code = bb.terminal_code
left join master.t_mtr_bank cc on
	aa.card_issuer = cc.bank_code
left join master.t_mtr_station dd on
	aa.station_code = dd.station_id
left join master.t_mtr_station ee on
	aa.station_code_in_before = ee.station_id
left join master.t_mtr_station ff on
	aa.station_code_out_before = ff.station_id
left join master.t_mtr_device_terminal gg on
	aa.terminal_code_in_before = gg.terminal_code
left join master.t_mtr_device_terminal hh on
	aa.terminal_code_out_before = hh.terminal_code
left join master.t_mtr_card_type ii on
	aa.card_type_id = ii.card_type_id
left join master.t_mtr_subs_card_registration jj on
	aa.card_number = jj.card_number
left join master.t_mtr_subs_card_type kk on
	jj.subs_card_type_id = kk.subs_card_type_id
left join master.t_mtr_family_trip_registration ll on
	aa.card_number = ll.card_number
where
	aa.status = 1
	and aa.card_type_id in(3, 4)
	and jj.subs_card_type_id = '11'
	and aa.created_on between '2023-07-25' and ('2023-07-25'::date + '1 day'::interval)

<?php
/*
 * @package     Proxy Country Sorter
 * @author      DSTAT | @DDoS_Filter
 * @copyright   https://www.copyright.gov/dmca/
 * @file        /proxy_sort.php
 * @version     1.0
 * @site        https://www.freeproxychecker.com/
 * @comment     Sorts Proxies into files named using the 2 letter country code abbreviation standard
*/

if (count($argv) !== 3) {
	echo "\nUsage:\n";
	echo 'php '.$argv['0']." /path/to/list.txt /save/directory/path/\n";
	die();
}
if (!is_dir($argv['2'])) {
	die("Save directory path doesn't exist.\n");
}
if (($proxylist = fopen($argv['1'], 'r')) !== false) {
	exec('rm '.$argv['2'].'*.txt'); // DELETES ALL .TXT FILES IN THE SAVE DIRECTORY!
	$i = 0;
	echo "\n ".$argv['0']." v1.0\n Author: @DDoS_Filter\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n";
	while (!feof($proxylist)) {
		$line = fgets($proxylist);
		$line = str_replace("\n",'',$line);
		if (strlen($line) > 0) {
			$line = str_replace(array("http://", "socks4://", "socks5://", "\n"), '', $line);
			list($host, $port) = explode(":", $line);
			$ch = curl_init();
			curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_URL, 'https://ipinfo.io/'.$host.'/country');
			curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_HEADER, false);
			curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_USERAGENT, 'Curl');
			curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_CONNECTTIMEOUT, 2);
			curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER, true);
			$result = curl_exec($ch);
			$result = str_replace("\n",'',$result);
			$http_info = curl_getinfo($ch);
			
			if ($http_info['http_code'] == 200 && strlen($result) == 2) {
				file_put_contents($argv['2'].$result.'.txt', $host.':'.$port."\n", FILE_APPEND);
				$i++;
			} else {
				echo "HTTP ERROR!\nhttp error #: ".$http_info."\nResponse: ".$result."\n";
			}
			@fclose($scan);
			echo '	('.$i.') Found ('.$result.") Proxy!\r";
		}
	}
	fclose($proxylist);
	echo "\nFinished Sorting Proxies!\n";
} else {
	die('Error: Unable to read list file.');
}

title: receber_imagem.php
content:
<?php
// Verifica se algum arquivo foi enviado
if (isset($_FILES['imagem']) && $_FILES['imagem']['error'] === 0) {
    // Informações sobre o arquivo
    $nomeArquivo = $_FILES['imagem']['name'];
    $tipoArquivo = $_FILES['imagem']['type'];
    $tamanhoArquivo = $_FILES['imagem']['size'];
    $caminhoTemporario = $_FILES['imagem']['tmp_name'];
    
    // Verifica se o arquivo é uma imagem
    $extensoesPermitidas = array("jpg", "jpeg", "png", "gif");
    $extensao = strtolower(pathinfo($nomeArquivo, PATHINFO_EXTENSION));
    if (in_array($extensao, $extensoesPermitidas)) {
        // Define o diretório onde a imagem será salva
        $diretorioDestino = "imagens/";
        $caminhoCompleto = $diretorioDestino . $nomeArquivo;
        
        // Move o arquivo temporário para o diretório de destino
        if (move_uploaded_file($caminhoTemporario, $caminhoCompleto)) {
            echo "Imagem enviada e salva com sucesso!";
        } else {
            echo "Erro ao salvar a imagem.";
        }
    } else {
        echo "Formato de arquivo não permitido. Envie uma imagem (jpg, jpeg, png ou gif).";
    }
} else {
    echo "Erro no envio da imagem.";
}
?>

title: RPG Maker VX Ace - Item Age Sorting Script
content:
#------------------------------------------------------------------------------#
# - Item Age Sorting Script - by NinjaChicle
#
# This script pushes the most recent obtained item to
# the first index in the item list.
#------------------------------------------------------------------------------#
module Sort_em_all
 SORT_ITEMS   = true
 SORT_WEAPONS = true
 SORT_ARMORS  = true
end
# Turn to false if you don't want a type of item to be sorted.
# For the sorting to take effect, obtain an item in your game.
#
# Doesn't work well on save files that existed before using this script.

module DataManager
  class << self
    alias :itemtastic_create_game_objects :create_game_objects
    alias :itemtastic_make_save_contents :make_save_contents 
    alias :itemtastic_extract_save_contents :extract_save_contents
  end
  
  def self.create_game_objects
    itemtastic_create_game_objects
    $awesome_items = []
    $awesome_weapons = []
    $awesome_armors = []
  end
  def self.make_save_contents
    contents = itemtastic_make_save_contents
    contents[:sorted_items]   = $awesome_items
    contents[:sorted_weapons] = $awesome_weapons
    contents[:sorted_armors]  = $awesome_armors
    contents
  end
  
  def self.extract_save_contents(contents)
    itemtastic_extract_save_contents(contents)
    $awesome_items = contents[:sorted_items]     || []
    $awesome_weapons = contents[:sorted_weapons] || []
    $awesome_armors = contents[:sorted_armors]   || []
  end
end

class Game_Party < Game_Unit
  alias sortastic_gain_item gain_item
  def gain_item(item, amount, include_equip = false)
    sortastic_gain_item(item, amount, include_equip)
      if item.is_a?(RPG::Item) && Sort_em_all::SORT_ITEMS == true
       $awesome_items ||= []
       $awesome_items = $game_party.all_items.select {|item| item.is_a?(RPG::Item) } if $awesome_items == []
        if $imported["TH_InstanceItems"] && TH::Instance_Items::Enable_Items == true
         $awesome_items.delete(@item_list[-1]) if $awesome_items.include?(@item_list[-1])
         $awesome_items.unshift(@item_list[-1]) unless amount < 0
        else
         $awesome_items.delete(item) if $awesome_items.include?(item)
         $awesome_items.unshift(item) unless amount < 0
        end
      elsif item.is_a?(RPG::Weapon) && Sort_em_all::SORT_WEAPONS == true
       $awesome_weapons ||= []
       $awesome_weapons = $game_party.all_items.select {|item| item.is_a?(RPG::Weapon) } if $awesome_weapons == []
        if $imported["TH_InstanceItems"] && TH::Instance_Items::Enable_Weapons == true
         $awesome_weapons.delete(@weapon_list[-1]) if $awesome_weapons.include?(@weapon_list[-1])
         $awesome_weapons.unshift(@weapon_list[-1]) unless amount < 0
        else
         $awesome_weapons.delete(item) if $awesome_weapons.include?(item)
         $awesome_weapons.unshift(item) unless amount < 0
        end
      elsif item.is_a?(RPG::Armor) && Sort_em_all::SORT_ARMORS == true
       $awesome_armors ||= []
       $awesome_armors = $game_party.all_items.select {|item| item.is_a?(RPG::Armor) } if $awesome_armors == []
        if $imported["TH_InstanceItems"] && TH::Instance_Items::Enable_Armors == true
         $awesome_armors.delete(@armor_list[-1]) if $awesome_armors.include?(@armor_list[-1])
         $awesome_armors.unshift(@armor_list[-1]) unless amount < 0
        else
         $awesome_armors.delete(item) if $awesome_armors.include?(item)
         $awesome_armors.unshift(item) unless amount < 0
        end
      end
  end
end

class Window_ItemList < Window_Selectable
  alias sortastic_make_item_list make_item_list
  def make_item_list
    sortastic_make_item_list
    if SceneManager.scene_is?(Scene_Item)
       if @data[0].is_a?(RPG::Weapon)
        if Sort_em_all::SORT_WEAPONS == true
         @data = $awesome_weapons.select {|item| include?(item) }
         @data.push(nil) if include?(nil)
        end
      elsif @data[0].is_a?(RPG::Armor)
        if Sort_em_all::SORT_ARMORS == true 
         @data = $awesome_armors.select {|item| include?(item) }
         @data.push(nil) if include?(nil)
        end
      else
        if Sort_em_all::SORT_ITEMS == true
        @data = $awesome_items.select {|item| include?(item) }
        @data.push(nil) if include?(nil)
        end
      end
    end
  end
end

select
	a.uid,
				a.card_activation_id,
				a.card_number,
				a.created_on as activation_date,
				a.valid_start,
				a.valid_end,
				b.bank_name,
				a.name,
				a.nik,
				d.station_name,
				a.station_code,
				e.terminal_name,
				a.terminal_code,
				f.terminal_type_name,
				a.fee,
				c.name_type as sub_card_type_name,
				a.user_id,
				a.status,
				a.activation_type,
				case
					when a.activation_type = 1 then 'Aktivasi'
		when a.activation_type = 2 then 'Tulis Ulang'
		when a.activation_type = 3 then 'Replacement'
		else null
	end as activation_type_name
from
	trx.t_trx_subs_card_activation a
left join master.t_mtr_bank b on
	a.card_issuer = b.bank_code
left join master.t_mtr_subs_card_type c on
	a.subs_card_type_id = c.subs_card_type_id
left join master.t_mtr_station d on
	a.station_code = d.station_id
left join master.t_mtr_device_terminal e on
	a.terminal_code = e.terminal_code
left join master.t_mtr_device_terminal_type f on
	e.terminal_type = f.terminal_type_code
where
	a.status in (1, 0)
	and(upper(a.uid) = upper('20054E27'))
	and(a.card_number = '7546800001150084')
	and(DATE(a.created_on) between '2023-07-24' and '2023-07-24' )
	
	
	select * from master.t_mtr_subs_card_type;

Jeg tror det politi rykte kommer fra Ulf og Linda.

Ikke glem at det var Linda som satt meg,, kåre i en kjempe psykose for ca 10 år siden.
Mange år etter det har jeg vært redd,, følt meg forfulgt.
Frykten og psykosen er borte nå.

Men hva med det noen av dere vet om men ikke forteller de andre.

De dere truer til stillhet. 
Dere truer folk med å miste unga sine. Hva faan er det dere holder på med. 

Folk flest veit faan ingen ting.


Sier bare en ting. 

Dette haster.

Mange kommer til å bli glade, noen ikke så glade.

Dere som ikke har direkte befatning med pappa har lite å frykte..

Ang americium.
Flere historier der.

Lurer på hvilke fæle ord og evnt video sekvenser dere blir servert.

Mange  blir rund lurt...

Mamma blir manipulert til å tro jeg er syk..
Hu blir manipulert og seksuelt misbrukt av. Gidder ikke si navn men de bor ikke langt unna.

Leste på en lapp mamma hadde sKrevet .

Quoted'

Naboene leder meg til å få kåre innlagt ,

Bekymringsmeldinger fra flere personer og instanser.

title: seprateListener
content:
import serial
import time
import multiprocessing

def send_command(ser, command):
    ser.write(command.encode())
    print(f"Sent command: {command}")

def receive_response(ser):
    while True:
        response = ser.readline().decode().strip()
        if response:
            print(f"Received response: {response}")

def main(port='/dev/ttyACM0', baudrate=9600, timeout=1):
    try:
        # Open the serial port
        ser = serial.Serial(port, baudrate, timeout=timeout)
        
        # Wait for the Arduino to initialize (optional)
        time.sleep(2)

        # Define commands to send
        commands = ["command1", "command2", "command3"]

        # Create a separate process to continuously listen for responses
        response_process = multiprocessing.Process(target=receive_response, args=(ser,))
        response_process.daemon = True
        response_process.start()

        # Send commands
        for command in commands:
            send_command(ser, command)

        # Close the serial port
        ser.close()
        print("Communication finished.")
    except Exception as e:
        print("Error:", str(e))

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

title: serialHoren

import serial
import time

def send_and_receive(port='/dev/ttyACM0', baudrate=9600, timeout=1):
    try:
        # Open the serial port
        ser = serial.Serial(port, baudrate, timeout=timeout)
        
        # Wait for the Arduino to initialize (optional)
        time.sleep(2)

        # Define commands to send
        commands = ["command1", "command2", "command3"]

        for command in commands:
            # Send the command
            ser.write(command.encode())
            print(f"Sent command: {command}")

            # Wait for a response
            response = ser.readline().decode().strip()
            print(f"Received response: {response}")

        # Close the serial port
        ser.close()
        print("Communication finished.")
    except Exception as e:
        print("Error:", str(e))

if __name__ == "__main__":
    send_and_receive()

from os import environ
environ['PYGAME_HIDE_SUPPORT_PROMPT'] = '1'
import pygame
from glob import glob
import time
running=True

clock = pygame.time.Clock()
images = [pygame.image.load(jpg) for jpg in glob("/home/pi/Bilder/*.jpg")]

pygame.init()
screen = pygame.display.set_mode((768, 576))
current_image = 1
screen.blit(images[current_image], (0,0))
pygame.display.flip()

def wait_or_quit(sek):
    global running
    start = time.time ()
    while time.time () < start + 5 :
        for event in pygame.event.get():
            if event.type == pygame.QUIT:
                running = False
                return
        pass

def crossfade(image1, image2):
    global running
    alpha_surface = pygame.Surface(screen.get_size(), pygame.SRCALPHA)
    for alpha in range(0, 52):
        for event in pygame.event.get():
                if event.type == pygame.QUIT:
                    running = False
                    return
        alpha_surface.blit(image1, (0,0))
        image2.set_alpha(alpha*5)
        alpha_surface.blit(image2, (0,0))
        screen.blit(alpha_surface,(0,0))
        pygame.display.flip()


while True:
    wait_or_quit(5)
    if running==False:
        break
    next_image = (current_image + 1) % len(images)
    crossfade(images[current_image], images[next_image])
    if running==False:
        break
    current_image=next_image

pygame.quit()

BWR - Changelog 24/07/23
content:
Engineer
  Fixed construction times to match intended speeds
Quick-Fix
+ Fixed uber draining while quickly switching and trying to activate
Panic Attack
+ Fixed Alt-Fire being activated when hauling a building with weapon out
Disciplinary Action
- Fixed holster penalty to be 100% slower (was 50%)
Fixes to changes to make these items perform consistently.

Short Circuit
- Reduced blast jump height by -33%
Jump height was deemed too extreme for the cost and easily exploitable. This height, just under a rocket jump, should be more than enough for the engineer.

Spy-cicle
  Restored HUD overlay when knife resistance is active
- Increased recharge time to 15s (was 10s)
The knive's benefits were seen as too spammable with minimal downside. Returning it to a longer time without a knife should make the decision to melt it more impactful.

Conniver's Kunai
+ Increased max health recovery to 1.5/s (was 1/s)
A tweak to lessen the downtime between stabs in order to gain its benefits.

Dead Ringer
+ No longer consumes 50% cloak if activated just as you're brought below 50% HP
- Added 20% cloak lost on decloak
Effect was deemed too spammable when taking damage below 50% HP. This minimum cloak lost should provide a decent enough window for the spy to be vulnerable without cloak if they choose to spam it.

Atomizer
+ Removed deploy penalty
+ Removed damage penalty
- Added: This weapon holsters 100% slower
These changes were done to help make the weapon work better as a finisher, and gain it's jump boost more readily. The slower holster would require more commitment out of it for either of its uses.

Force-a-Nature
+ Added: +20% damage vs targets launched by this weapon's knockback
- Removed accuracy bonus on targets launched airborne
- Removed faster reload speed bonus (was 15%)
The accuracy bonus was not seen as particularly useful in taking out tarets with a second shot. This simpler bonus should be easier to understand and allows the scout to better commit to high burst damage against a target. Reverting its reload speed should help better pace the damage the scout can output.

Soda Popper
+ Reverted reload speed bonus to 25% (was 15%)
+ Reverted On Hit: Builds Hype
+ Perform extra air jumps with 15% Hype
  Hype no longer activates with alt-fire
- Added: No double jump
- Removed replenishing jumps with damage in air
The former jump refresh mechanic was seen as clunky and hard to pull off. In trying to make it more easier to understand and tying it to the old Hype meter, the user is instead granted the ability to spend Hype for extra jumps with damage dealt. As a downside, the Scout loses his on-demand air jump and turns his boosted vertical mobility into a resource he better needs to manage.
